<br>
<br>
Qandaar<br>
7th level Magician<br>
Karana Server <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qandaar>Qandaar</A> at: 5/6/02 11:01:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udionia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dionia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#333333>(5/8/02 12:34:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=376.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dungeon Tactics Please?</span><hr size=1> Watch and learn the pathing, for one. Some dungeons are really obvious, but there do exist strange track inconsistencies. My favorite one is in the alcove at the front of Splitpaw, where Kober will run from the alcove to the double doors and back just to hit a mob that's right in front of me. Or the throne room in the Warrens, where the pathing is a square circuit of straight lines. You can sometimes exploit these, but I wouldn't recommend it.  <p><br><i>Signing off from <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.quickJumpTo?id=thecrossroadstavern8833">Zebuxoruk the Ungod</a></i>
